Instructions: [        1) Act as a software requirements engineer tasked to elicit system requirements of an application.        1) Generate only 5 additional questions first that would help more accurately answer the question         2) The questions should be in JSON format with a question ID        3) Use the delimiter 'SEP' after printing the additional questions.    ]    Task: [        You have to generate at least 50 system requirements in form of user stories for the County Services application whose description is given below. You must display the additional questions first in JSON format, before generating the requirements. Generate an ID as well for the requirements.     ]     Description = [        Our application, named County Services Portal, is a comprehensive online platform designed to facilitate efficient and transparent interactions between the County and its various stakeholders. The main objective of the application is to streamline the process of accessing and managing county services, processes, and information. It caters to a wide range of end users, including Public Users, Prospective Applicants, Customers, Applicants, Staff members, Planning Staff members, Zoning Staff members, Plan Review Staff members, Development Staff members, Inspection Staff members, and Enforcement Staff members.        Public Users can easily search for publicly available information related to properties, county services, processes, and general information. Prospective Applicants can research requirements and select the appropriate service or application type via the online portal. Applicants have the ability to request pre-application assistance and receive responses to their inquiries. Customers can create user accounts on the Customer Portal to perform transactions that require authentication, such as fee payments and application submissions.                Applicants can submit their applications, including information, plans, and supporting documentation, to initiate transactions with the County. They can also check the status of their transactions and modify their applications when necessary. Staff members have various capabilities within the system, including performing completeness reviews, recording internal notes, assigning applications for detailed review, applying and removing holds, sending formal responses to applicants, tracking draft proffers, managing approved proffers and ordinances, scheduling meetings, denoting application statuses, conducting and tracking plan amendments and planning studies, generating planning-related reports, evaluating consistency with the comprehensive plan, performing staff reviews, processing requests for zoning information, issuing zoning-related permits, developing staff reports, managing hearing calendars, assigning hearing dates, managing affidavits, preparing for and supporting hearing execution, capturing hearing decisions, processing appeals, assigning plans for review, managing plan reviewer workload, and conducting plan review meetings with applicants.                Furthermore, the application enables Development Staff members to issue development-related permits, manage bonds, and oversee the completion of building development projects. Inspection Staff members can create and assign inspections, while Inspection Staff Supervisors ensure appropriate workload distribution. Inspectors conduct inspections, ensuring compliance with codes and regulations, and provide results to customers. Enforcement Staff members have the ability to issue notices of violation and citations, recording formal communication with responsible parties.                The County Services Portal also includes features such as property information search, notifications for geospatial attribute changes, custom query/report creation, condo unit creation, updates to GIS property management, and sending/posting citations and fines.                Overall, the County Services Portal aims to improve accessibility, efficiency, and communication throughout the entire lifecycle of county services and processes. It empowers both the public and county staff members by providing a centralized platform for information, transactions, collaboration, and decision-making, ultimately enhancing the overall experience for all stakeholders involved.    ]    Output Format: [        {'QUE1': 'abc?', ..., 'QUE5': 'xyz?'
}        SEP        {'REQ1': 'abc', ..., 'REQ50': 'xyz'
}    ]

