Instructions: [        1) Act as a software requirements engineer tasked to elicit system requirements of an application.        1) Generate only 5 additional questions first that would help more accurately answer the question         2) The questions should be in JSON format with a question ID        3) Use the delimiter 'SEP' after printing the additional questions.    ]    Task: [        You have to generate at least 50 system requirements in form of user stories for the EcoRecycle application whose description is given below. You must display the additional questions first in JSON format, before generating the requirements. Generate an ID as well for the requirements.     ]     Description = [    Our application, EcoRecycle, is a user-friendly web platform designed to promote recycling and facilitate sustainable waste management. The primary objective of EcoRecycle is to connect users with nearby recycling facilities and provide them with comprehensive information on recycling options in their area. By entering their zip code, users can easily access a list of nearby recycling facilities, including information on accepted recyclable materials and their corresponding opening hours. To ensure convenience, users have the option to select flexible pick-up times and view the facilities on a map, enabling them to plan their recycling activities efficiently. Furthermore, users can create an account and personalize their profiles by adding favorite donation centers, allowing for easy access to preferred locations. EcoRecycle also offers email notifications for new events and maintains a database of public recycling bins, special waste drop-off sites, and safe disposal events, which users can browse on the platform. The application prioritizes a great user interface and experience, ensuring a pleasant and intuitive interaction for users across all devices. In addition to the user-focused features, EcoRecycle includes administrative functionalities such as updating recycling facility information, monitoring user feedback and complaints, and managing user activities. Admins can also access a comprehensive dashboard that provides real-time usage statistics and site statuses, aiding in decision-making and improving service quality. Moreover, the application ensures data security by encrypting all sensitive information, safeguarding against potential breaches. EcoRecycle serves various user groups, including individuals seeking recycling options, employees navigating neighborhoods for work purposes, developers integrating the application's API, and executives and HR personnel who require access to performance data and employee information, respectively. By addressing the diverse needs of users, admins, and recycling facilities, EcoRecycle strives to promote sustainable practices, foster community engagement, and contribute to a greener future.    ]    Output Format: [        {'QUE1': 'abc?', ..., 'QUE5': 'xyz?'
}        SEP        {'REQ1': 'abc', ..., 'REQ50': 'xyz'
}    ]

