a visualisations, So that I can find guidance in creating my own with Open Spending.', 'REQ48': 'As a Data Publishing User, I want to know if my CSV file is valid, So that I can fix possible data issues before publishing it on Open Spending.', 'REQ49': 'As a Data Consuming User, I want to be able to search any dataset published and publicly accessible by their title and metadata, So that I can find the datasets I'm interested in.', 'REQ50': 'As a Data Consuming User, I want to visualize by default in treemap, bubble tree, map and pivot table the most recent year when my dataset contain multiple years, So that I'm not confused with the amounts.', 'REQ51': 'As an API user, I want to be able to change the colors of the embedded visualisations in my own platform, So that I can customize the visualisations.', 'REQ52': 'As an API user, I want to be able to change some of the styling of the embedded Viewer in my own platform, So that I can brand it to my own organisation's color scheme.', 'REQ53': 'As a Platform administrator, I want to be able to translate the data types hierarchies of the Viewer while in embed mode, So that my users can understand the interface in their native language.'
