      For site administrators, AgileHub provides tools to review and approve training and certification applications, ensuring that only qualified individuals become Certified Scrum Practitioners or Certified Scrum Trainers. Administrators can also edit member profiles, manage help wanted ads, and oversee the publication of news articles. The application includes a dedicated FAQ section to address common queries, and site members can download training materials, PDFs, and presentations for their reference.                AgileHub aims to cater to the diverse needs of the Scrum community, including recruiters who can post job ads, trainers who can access trainer-specific information, and site visitors who can stay up-to-date with the latest news and upcoming events. The platform offers seamless navigation, a user-friendly interface, and features such as RSS feeds and email notifications to ensure users can easily access relevant content and updates. Whether you are an aspiring Scrum practitioner, a seasoned trainer, a site member looking to connect with like-minded individuals, or a visitor seeking valuable resources, AgileHub is the go-to application for all things Scrum.    ]    Output Format: [        {'QUE1': 'abc?', ..., 'QUE5': 'xyz?'
}        SEP        {'REQ1': 'abc', ..., 'REQ50': 'xyz'
}    ]

