Instructions: [        1) Act as a software requirements engineer tasked to elicit system requirements of an application.        1) Generate only 5 additional questions first that would help more accurately answer the question         2) The questions should be in JSON format with a question ID        3) Use the delimiter 'SEP' after printing the additional questions.    ]    Task: [        You have to generate at least 50 system requirements in form of user stories for the Agile Estimation application whose description is given below. You must display the additional questions first in JSON format, before generating the requirements. Generate an ID as well for the requirements.     ]     Description = [    The Agile Estimation Application is a web-based tool designed to facilitate collaborative estimation sessions for Agile teams. It aims to streamline the estimation process and provide a seamless experience for moderators, estimators, participants, developers, and researchers. The application allows moderators to create and manage estimation games by entering a game name and optional description, and then inviting estimators through a unique URL. Moderators can start rounds by entering items to be estimated in a multi-line text field, and they have the flexibility to add, edit, or delete items as needed. The estimates are shown immediately, and the moderator can accept the average estimate or manually enter the agreed-upon estimate. The application supports re-estimation of stories and allows for importing and copying/pasting stories from spreadsheets for faster setup. Moderators can also browse previous games, view transcripts, and export them as HTML or CSV files. Account creation, login, and management functionalities are available for moderators. The application provides localized date and time display and offers password reminders via email. Moderators can choose the estimation scale, either modified Fibonacci sequence or powers of 2. The application accommodates up to 15 estimators, and participants can change their estimates until the last person selects a card. The two-minute countdown timer helps limit discussion time, and prior estimates are visible for comparison. Developers have focused on compliance with XHTML and CSS standards, database optimization, cross-browser compatibility, and adherence to W3C accessibility guidelines. The user experience emphasizes responsiveness, Unicode support, sensible URLs, and user-friendly error pages. The application also anonymizes results for research purposes and provides usage metrics for monitoring. The Agile Estimation Application is a comprehensive solution that aims to enhance estimation collaboration, improve efficiency, and provide valuable insights for Agile teams.    ]    Output Format: [        {'QUE1': 'abc?', ..., 'QUE5': 'xyz?'
}        SEP        {'REQ1': 'abc', ..., 'REQ50': 'xyz'
}    ]

Instructions: [        1) Act as a software requirements engineer tasked to elicit system requirements of an application.        1) Generate only 5 additional questions first that would help more accurately answer the question         2) The questions should be in JSON format with a question ID        3) Use the delimiter 'SEP' after printing the additional questions.    ]    Task: [        You have to generate at least 50 system requirements in form of user stories for the Data Package Publisher application whose description is given below. You must display the additional questions first in JSON format, before generating the requirements. Generate an ID as well for the requirements.     ]     Description = [        The Data Package Publisher is a comprehensive application that enables users, such as publishers, visitors, consumers, data analysts, developers, and administrators, to efficiently publish, manage, and access datasets. With the objective of facilitating dataset sharing and collaboration, the application offers a user-friendly interface and powerful functionality.        The motivation behind the Data Package Publisher is to provide a centralized platform where publishers can easily publish datasets according to their specific requirements. Publishers can choose between two options: publishing datasets privately, accessible only to a select group of people, or sharing them publicly with everyone. To begin using the application, publishers can sign up for an account using their GitHub or Google credentials, reducing the need for manual data entry and password management.                Once registered, publishers are guided on the next steps to take, ensuring a smooth onboarding experience. They can import their data packages into the registry, configuring their clients and using a publish command to update existing datasets, or unpublish and delete data packages if needed. The application emphasizes data validation, allowing publishers to validate data before publication and ensuring the accuracy and quality of the datasets. Real-time validation feedback is provided, enabling publishers to address any issues promptly.                For consumers, the Data Package Publisher offers a reliable and user-friendly environment for discovering, viewing, and downloading datasets. Consumers can search for data packages based on descriptions, view datasets online, and download them as a single file, eliminating the need for manual resource retrieval. They can also access comprehensive information about each data package, including download statistics, versioning details, and changes in schema, empowering them to make informed decisions about dataset usage.                Furthermore, the application supports collaboration and data management within organizations. Publishers can invite users to join their platform, manage roles and permissions, and maintain a clear overview of their organization's members. The application's administrative capabilities enable administrators to configure key parameters, monitor usage metrics, and implement a pricing plan and billing system to ensure the platform's sustainability.                Overall, the Data Package Publisher caters to the diverse needs of publishers, consumers, data analysts, developers, and administrators, providing an intuitive and powerful platform for dataset publication, management, and access. With features like data validation, version control, collaboration support, and comprehensive metadata, the application promotes efficient and reliable data sharing, driving data-driven insights and fostering a vibrant data community.    ]    Output Format: [        {'QUE1': 'abc?', ..., 'QUE5': 'xyz?'
}        SEP        {'REQ1': 'abc', ..., 'REQ50': 'xyz'
}    ]

