Instructions: [        1) Act as a software requirements engineer tasked to elicit system requirements of an application.        1) Generate only 5 additional questions first that would help more accurately answer the question         2) The questions should be in JSON format with a question ID        3) Use the delimiter 'SEP' after printing the additional questions.    ]    Task: [        You have to generate at least 50 system requirements in form of user stories for the ALFRED (Assisted Living Framework for the Elderly) application whose description is given below. You must display the additional questions first in JSON format, before generating the requirements. Generate an ID as well for the requirements.     ]     Description = [        ALFRED (Assisted Living Framework for the Elderly) is an innovative application designed to meet the diverse needs of older adults. The objective of ALFRED is to provide a user-friendly and personalized experience while ensuring privacy and control over personal data. This application caters specifically to older individuals, offering speech technology for communication, well-visible buttons for easy interaction, and comprehensive privacy and data management settings. ALFRED is available across multiple devices, including wearable options like bracelets or necklaces, as well as computers, tablets, and phones. The application is designed to be accessible and adaptable, with features for users with visual or hearing impairments. ALFRED provides support for various activities, such as information retrieval, entertainment, home automation, health monitoring, social connections, and transportation assistance. Users can navigate, pay for small amounts, control home devices, stay updated on news, communicate with friends and family, and receive emergency assistance when needed. ALFRED also promotes physical and mental well-being by offering exercise routines, memory games, and personalized health tips. The application enables customization based on user preferences and interests and continuously adapts to changing user demands by offering new apps on the ALFREDO platform. ALFRED ensures a user-friendly experience through clear instructions, ongoing service support, and an introductory conversation to help users familiarize themselves with the application. It is available at senior shops with specialized client support and aims to be affordable for older individuals. ALFRED aims to bridge the gap between older adults and technology, promoting real interaction with humans while utilizing ICT tools to enhance their daily lives.    ]    Output Format: [        {'QUE1': 'abc?', ..., 'QUE5': 'xyz?'
}        SEP        {'REQ1': 'abc', ..., 'REQ50': 'xyz'
}    ]

