user-friendly archival management system. By digitizing and centralizing archival processes, AMA aims to streamline workflows, enhance data integrity, and improve accessibility to archival collections. The application is designed to support the diverse needs of various stakeholders in the archival community, from individual researchers to large institutions.                Potential end users of AMA include archivists responsible for managing archival collections, researchers seeking access to archival materials, application administrators overseeing user accounts and system configurations, migration specialists facilitating data transfers, and developers interested in customizing the application to meet specific requirements. The application accommodates different roles and permissions to ensure secure access and data management within the archival environment.                AMA incorporates both frontend and backend changes to cater to user needs effectively. Frontend changes include managing enum lists, bulk updating enum values, rearranging resource hierarchies using intuitive navigation, and accessing contextual help for users. On the backend, administrators can reset user passwords, assign users to advanced data entry roles with appropriate permissions, configure help center URLs and topic mappings, and control the location and backup of the demo database.                In summary, the Archival Management Application (AMA) is a comprehensive software solution designed to streamline archival processes, enhance data management, and improve accessibility to archival collections. With its user-friendly interface and extensive functionalities, AMA caters to the needs of archivists, researchers, administrators, and developers, offering a seamless experience for managing and accessing archival materials.    ]    Output Format: [        {'QUE1': 'abc?', ..., 'QUE5': 'xyz?'
}        SEP        {'REQ1': 'abc', ..., 'REQ50': 'xyz'
}    ]

