Instructions: [        1) Act as a software requirements engineer tasked to elicit system requirements of an application.        1) Generate only 5 additional questions first that would help more accurately answer the question         2) The questions should be in JSON format with a question ID        3) Use the delimiter 'SEP' after printing the additional questions.    ]    Task: [        You have to generate at least 50 system requirements in form of user stories for the Digital Asset Management application whose description is given below. You must display the additional questions first in JSON format, before generating the requirements. Generate an ID as well for the requirements.     ]     Description = [        Our application, the Digital Asset Management System (DAMS), is a comprehensive solution designed to meet the needs of repository managers, DAMS managers, and end users in managing and accessing digital collections and objects. The primary objectives of the application are to provide repository managers with custodial control and management capabilities, ensure efficient and synchronized updates across all relevant information, and offer enhanced access and search functionalities for end users.         Motivated by the need for centralized repository management, our application enables repository managers to have a holistic view of the collections and objects for which they are responsible. They can easily update repository information in one place, knowing that the changes will be propagated consistently throughout the system. The application also allows repository managers to enforce access constraints, ensuring that only staff members of their unit and DAMS managers with universal access have curatorial privileges for their unit's assets.                For end users, the application offers comprehensive browsing and search capabilities. Users can browse and list all collections and objects within the DAMS belonging to a specific library unit. Additionally, they can contact repositories directly for inquiries or further information. The DAMS manager benefits from the ability to list and browse formal collections, along with their relationships, providing a comprehensive overview of the DAMS content.                The application provides repository managers with various tools to manage collections and objects effectively. They can identify and group collections based on provenance, create collections from existing collections and objects, and establish relationships between different collections. Repository managers can describe collections and objects in detail, including titles, dates, languages, and other relevant aspects. They can also indicate associated names, subjects, external descriptions, and events related to the collections and objects.                Furthermore, the application caters to the needs of repository managers in managing object components and content files. Repository managers can track and manage the components and files belonging to objects, describing them and indicating relevant information such as titles, dates, languages, copyright status, licenses, and rights. They can also represent the physical and logical structure of objects, link components and files, and ensure the integrity and authenticity of content files.                DAMS managers have access to features specifically designed for preservation management. They can monitor the integrity and obsolescence of master files by tracking aspects such as file size, creation date, file format, format version, checksums, and source-capture information. The application also enables DAMS managers to identify objects requiring attention, either due to integrity concerns or the need to update to a more current file format.                With its comprehensive features and user-friendly interface, our application serves as a powerful tool for repository managers, DAMS managers, and end users, facilitating efficient management, discovery, and access to digital collections and objects. Whether it's providing custodial control, enforcing access constraints, or enabling extensive search and browsing capabilities, our application aims to streamline the management and accessibility of digital assets while ensuring accurate and up-to-date information for all stakeholders.    ]    Output Format: [        {'QUE1': 'abc?', ..., 'QUE5': 'xyz?'
}        SEP        {'REQ1': 'abc', ..., 'REQ50': 'xyz'
}    ]

